{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775858815168,"sessionID":"ses_286917275ffeVx3USWNLrvoLju","part":{"id":"prt_d796f0b36001Bzavk0LfHXji4X","messageID":"msg_d796ef79d001bkG0uobmlVie6S","sessionID":"ses_286917275ffeVx3USWNLrvoLju","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-d2cf8541ccb34b2bb3ed10cfbff823bf","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-015/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-015/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # PicoD 命令执行 API Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: [To be filled during spec definition]\n5: \n6: ## Requirements\n7: [To be filled during spec definition]\n\n(End of file - total 7 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# PicoD 命令执行 API Specification\n\n## Purpose\n[To be filled during spec definition]\n\n## Requirements\n[To be filled during spec definition]","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-015/spec.md","time":{"start":1775858815146,"end":1775858815166}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775858815169,"sessionID":"ses_286917275ffeVx3USWNLrvoLju","part":{"id":"prt_d796f0dda001yP7mCRR2422DVr","messageID":"msg_d796ef79d001bkG0uobmlVie6S","sessionID":"ses_286917275ffeVx3USWNLrvoLju","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-b5e838a8f1774f4993c8fb9d4a300c88","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-015/design.md","limit":100},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-015/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # PicoD 命令执行 API Design\n2: \n3: ## AR-015 — PicoD 命令执行 API\n4: \n5: **Module**: `pkg/picod`\n6: **Language**: Go\n7: **Purpose**: Implement a secure HTTP daemon for command execution and file management within a configurable workspace jail, providing JWT-protected APIs for code interpreter sandboxes in the AgentCube platform.\n8: \n9: ## Overview\n10: \n11: PicoD is an HTTP daemon that runs commands inside a configurable workspace jail, manages workspace files, and exposes a health endpoint with JWT (RSA)–protected APIs. It serves as the core execution engine for code interpreter sandboxes, enabling secure code execution, file operations (upload, list, download), and health monitoring with proper authentication.\n12: \n13: ### Key Requirements\n14: \n15: - HTTP server with configurable port and workspace directory\n16: - JWT (RSA) authentication for all API endpoints except health check\n17: - Command execution API with timeout support\n18: - File management APIs (upload, list, download)\n19: - Path security to enforce workspace jail\n20: - Support for multipart and JSON Base64 file uploads\n21: - Comprehensive error handling and logging\n22: - Zero-downtime deployment support with graceful shutdown\n23: \n24: ## Architecture\n25: \n26: ### Package Structure\n27: \n28: ```\n29: pkg/picod/\n30: ├── auth.go                # JWT authentication manager and middleware\n31: ├── execute.go             # Command execution handler\n32: ├── files.go               # File upload, list, download handlers\n33: ├── server.go              # Server initialization and configuration\n34: ├── handlers.go            # HTTP handler functions\n35: ├── middleware.go          # Custom middleware\n36: ├── errors.go              # Error types and handling\n37: ├── config.go              # Configuration structs\n38: └── constants.go           # Constants and defaults\n39: \n40: cmd/picod/\n41: ├── main.go                # CLI entry point\n42: └── flags.go               # CLI flag definitions\n43: ```\n44: \n45: ### Component Interactions\n46: \n47: ```\n48: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n49: │                         PicoD HTTP Server                        │\n50: │                                                                  │\n51: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n52: │  │              Gin HTTP Engine                             │   │\n53: │  │  - Global middleware: Logger, Recovery                   │   │\n54: │  │  - API routes with JWT auth                              │   │\n55: │  │  - Health endpoint (no auth)                             │   │\n56: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n57: │                                                                  │\n58: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n59: │  │              Auth Manager                                │   │\n60: │  │  - JWT validation with RSA public key                    │   │\n61: │  │  - AuthMiddleware for /api/* routes                     │   │\n62: │  │  - Request body size limiting                            │   │\n63: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n64: │                                                                  │\n65: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n66: │  │              Request Handlers                            │   │\n67: │  │  - ExecuteHandler: Command execution                     │   │\n68: │  │  - UploadFileHandler: File upload                        │   │\n69: │  │  - ListFilesHandler: Directory listing                   │   │\n70: │  │  - DownloadFileHandler: File download                    │   │\n71: │  │  - HealthCheckHandler: Health status                     │   │\n72: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n73: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n74:            │                     │                     │\n75:            │                     │                     │\n76:            ▼                     ▼                     ▼\n77:  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐\n78:  │  File System     │  │     OS Exec      │  │     JWT Keys     │\n79:  │  (Workspace Jail)│  │  (Commands)      │  │  (Auth)          │\n80:  │  - Files         │  │  - Contexts      │  │  - RSA Public    │\n81:  │  - Directories   │  │  - Timeouts      │  │  - Validation    │\n82:  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────┘\n83: ```\n84: \n85: ### Request Flow\n86: \n87: ```\n88: HTTP Request\n89:     ↓\n90: [Global Middleware] Logger, Recovery\n91:     ↓\n92: [Route Matching] Check endpoint\n93:     ↓\n94: [Auth Middleware?] If /api/* path:\n95:     ↓ Yes                      ↓ No (/health)\n96: [JWT Validation]              [Process Request]\n97:     - Parse Authorization        - Health check\n98:     - Verify RSA signature\n99:     - Check expiration\n100:     ↓\n\n(Showing lines 1-100 of 1338. Use offset=101 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# PicoD 命令执行 API Design\n\n## AR-015 — PicoD 命令执行 API\n\n**Module**: `pkg/picod`\n**Language**: Go\n**Purpose**: Implement a secure HTTP daemon for command execution and file management within a configurable workspace jail, providing JWT-protected APIs for code interpreter sandboxes in the AgentCube platform.\n\n## Overview\n\nPicoD is an HTTP daemon that runs commands inside a configurable workspace jail, manages workspace files, and exposes a health endpoint with JWT (RSA)–protected APIs. It serves as the core execution engine for code interpreter sandboxes, enabling secure code execution, file operations (upload, list, download), and health monitoring with proper authentication.\n\n### Key Requirements\n\n- HTTP server with configurable port and workspace directory\n- JWT (RSA) authentication for all API endpoints except health check\n- Command execution API with timeout support\n- File management APIs (upload, list, download)\n- Path security to enforce workspace jail\n- Support for multipart and JSON Base64 file uploads","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-015/design.md","time":{"start":1775858815150,"end":1775858815168}}}}
