 MiB)\n37: - [ ] Define default value constants:\n38:   - [ ] `DefaultPort = 8080`\n39:   - [ ] `DefaultTimeout = 60 * time.Second`\n40:   - [ ] `DefaultFileMode = 0644`\n41:   - [ ] `DefaultDirMode = 0755`\n42:   - [ ] `MaxFileMode = 0777`\n43:   - [ ] `ReadHeaderTimeout = 10 * time.Second`\n44: - [ ] Define version constants:\n45:   - [ ] `ServiceName = \"PicoD\"`\n46:   - [ ] `Version = \"0.0.1\"`\n47: - [ ] Define HTTP header constants:\n48:   - [ ] `HeaderAuthorization = \"Authorization\"`\n49:   - [ ] `HeaderContentDescription = \"Content-Description\"`\n50:   - [ ] `HeaderContentDisposition = \"Content-Disposition\"`\n51:   - [ ] `HeaderContentEncoding = \"Content-Transfer-Encoding\"`\n52:   - [ ] `HeaderContentType = \"Content-Type\"`\n53: - [ ] Define MIME type constants:\n54:   - [ ] `MIMEOctetStream = \"application/octet-stream\"`\n55:   - [ ] `MIMEMultipart = \"multipart/form-data\"`\n56: - [ ] Define error message constants:\n57:   - [ ] `ErrMsgMissingAuthHeader = \"Missing Authorization header\"`\n58:   - [ ] `ErrMsgInvalidAuthFormat = \"Use Bearer <token> format\"`\n59:   - [ ] `ErrMsgInvalidToken = \"Invalid token\"`\n60:   - [ ] `ErrMsgEmptyCommand = \"command cannot be empty\"`\n61:   - [ ] `ErrMsgMissingPathParam = \"Missing 'path' query parameter\"`\n62:   - [ ] `ErrMsgDirectoryNotFound = \"Directory not found\"`\n63:   - [ ] `ErrMsgFileNotFound = \"File not found\"`\n64:   - [ ] `ErrMsgPathIsDirectory = \"Path is a directory, not a file\"`\n65:   - [ ] `ErrMsgAccessDenied = \"Access denied: path escapes workspace\"`\n66:   - [ ] `ErrMsgInvalidWorkingDir = \"Invalid working directory: \"`\n67:   - [ ] `ErrMsgWorkspaceNotInit = \"workspace directory not initialized\"`\n68:   - [ ] `ErrMsgInvalidBase64 = \"invalid base64 encoding\"`\n69: \n70: **Verification**: Run `go test ./pkg/picod -run TestConstants` to verify all constants are defined\n71: \n72: ---\n73: \n74: ### Task 3: Define error types in errors.go\n75: - [ ] Define error constants:\n76:   - [ ] Validation errors: `ErrInvalidCommand`, `ErrEmptyCommand`, `ErrInvalidTimeout`, `ErrInvalidWorkingDir`, `ErrInvalidBase64`, `ErrMissingPath`\n77:   - [ ] File system errors: `ErrFileNotFound`, `ErrDirectoryNotFound`, `ErrPathIsDirectory`, `ErrAccessDenied`\n78:   - [ ] Authentication errors: `ErrMissingAuthHeader`, `ErrInvalidAuthFormat`, `ErrInvalidToken`, `ErrInvalidSignature`, `ErrTokenExpired`, `ErrInvalidPublicKey`\n79:   - [ ] Server errors: `ErrServerInternal`, `ErrWorkspaceNotInit`\n80: - [ ] Define `PicoDError` struct:\n81:   - [ ] `Code string`\n82:   - [ ] `Message string`\n83:   - [ ] `Detail string`\n84:   - [ ] `Err error`\n85: - [ ] Implement `Error()` method for `PicoDError`\n86: - [ ] Implement `Unwrap()` method for `PicoDError`\n87: - [ ] Define `ErrorResponse` struct:\n88:   - [ ] `Error string`\n89:   - [ ] `Code int`\n90:   - [ ] `Detail string` (optional)\n91: - [ ] Define error code constants:\n92:   - [ ] `ErrorCodeBadRequest = \"BadRequest\"`\n93:   - [ ] `ErrorCodeUnauthorized = \"Unauthorized\"`\n94:   - [ ] `ErrorCodeNotFound = \"NotFound\"`\n95:   - [ ] `ErrorCodeInternalError = \"InternalError\"`\n96: - [ ] Define `statusCodeMap` for error code to HTTP status mapping\n97: - [ ] Implement `NewError()` function to create `PicoDError` instances\n98: - [ ] Implement `HandleError()` function for consistent error responses\n99: \n100: **Verification**: Run `go test ./pkg/picod -run TestErrors` to verify error types work correctly\n\n(Showing lines 1-100 of 741. Use offset=101 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-015 — PicoD 命令执行 API Implementation Tasks\n\n**Module**: `pkg/picod`\n**Language**: Go\n**Size**: M\n**Design Stage**: ST-3 Completed\n\n## Task Breakdown\n\n### Task 1: Create pkg/picod package structure\n- [ ] Create `pkg/picod` directory\n- [ ] Create `pkg/picod/constants.go` file\n- [ ] Create `pkg/picod/config.go` file\n- [ ] Create `pkg/picod/errors.go` file\n- [ ] Create `pkg/picod/auth.go` file\n- [ 